# Instance internals

## The Nitro System

Offloads networking / storage / security to **Nitro cards** + a thin hypervisor:

- **Near bare-metal** perf; up to **100–200 Gbps**
- **Hardware EBS encryption**, no CPU cost
- Hard **security boundary** — no operator path into guest RAM
- Enables **bare metal** (`*.metal`) instances

## Tenancy

**Shared** (default, cheapest) · **Dedicated Instance** (your account) · **Dedicated Host** (a physical server — socket licensing / audits).

## Placement & lifecycle

**Placement groups:** cluster (low latency) · spread (resilience) · partition (racks).
**Stop** keeps EBS · **Hibernate** saves RAM to disk · **Terminate** deletes it.
